manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: EFSHREE Vacuum cleaners are a must-have for effective and time-saving cleaning around the house. A good vacuum cleaner should naturally offer powerful suction, a good grip, and a compact design to help you store it anywhere possible. Still, it can get a bit tricky to pick which works best for you once you start to delve into all the different types of models, brands, and accessories each vacuum comes with. This vacuum is right one for your home.

Wall-Mounted Storage The corded vacuum can be hung on the wall after cleaning is over. Makes your storage even easier and save your space. Easy to Use Easy to disassemble, turn left to open the dust cup. Washable Hepa Filter Filters of the hardwood floor vacuum can be detached for convenient clean and wash. Regular cleaning them to ensure your vacuum cleaner efficient. Please note, you should replace HEPA once a month or two.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great at getting in corners
reviews.reviewText: This vacuum has good suction, and does a great job getting dust out of corners. It's also excellent for cleaning stairs, because it's able to reach all the way into the corners of each step. It's lightweight, and has several different attachments. The one thing I don't care for is the air. This vacuum blows air out as it cleans just like any other vacuum. Except this one blows it right in my face. I tried moving it, and holding it a different way, but it doesn't seem to make a difference. I have really bad allergies. So having air with any little amount of dust blowing right at me is never a good thing. I don't think it would be okay even if I didn't have allergies. It's easy to use, and I didn't really have to assemble it, which was nice. The directions are terrible. They explain how to clean it. That part is okay, but they don't explain what works best for different surfaces, or how to operate it. This isn't my first vacuum so I was able to figure out how to use it without too much difficulty. But a little guidance with a machine I had never used before would have been appreciated.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 🌟Even Picks Up Pet Hair!!
reviews.reviewText: I got this Vacuum Cleaner around a month ago & have been utilizing it ever since. Yep, cleaning away.😅 This is actually a nice little unit that works quite well. Very flexible with a 180 degree back & forth/sideways rotation plus a 90 degree up & down. It is easy to hold & light weight. Has a 600 Watt Motor & a Hepa Filtration System. Comes with an easy to clean/washable filter(plus 1 extra) and 7L capacity.This has been/is quite handy unit to to have around. We’ve used it for all kinds of quick cleanup, touch ups & preps. Best part is that my son likes to use it. 😯 Yep… you heard that correctly. All I know is Mom isn’t arguing!😆 I’ve added some pics… Please excuse it Not being completely clean/new when I did so. He had already used it immediately after opening the box.😅 The small hairs come from our chigle(chihuahua + beagle), which is a testament to just how good the suction is. If you have pets then you know that their shed fur is the worst to try & clean. It does a really good job with it. Coffee grounds, grit/sand… I was impressed for a small model & good price….. am Definitely satisfied with this purchase.👍🏻🌟Recommend 100%❤️‍🔥Shalom…

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It's an average vacuum
reviews.reviewText: Before saying anything else, I'll say it's an average vacuum for this price range. I've used better, but I've used a lot worse.The build quality is pretty cheap, after a while of interchanging parts, they don't stay together as well anymore. You may need to tape them.The suction power works well on hardwood floors but sucks on carpets (pun intended).That being said, it does come with attachments that make it easier to clean hard-to-reach places.The weight is average, so it's not light but it's easy to use for long periods.It's easy to clean out when it's full.Overall, a cheap basic vacuum that does an okay job on hardwood but terrible on carpet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Its a good starter vac
reviews.reviewText: I got it for my daughters room which is small and pricing wasn't bad. The suction for this vacuum performs well on this device if the attachment had a little bit of revision. It does great when you attach the small brush fitting to clean out crumbs from the couch, but lacks once you place the long hose. You can feel the heat from the plastic housing if you use it for an extended period of time. Overall, I'm pleased at the product performance in small spaces.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was eager to get this vacuum for cleaning up crumbs in the kitchen and cleaning the car. Unfortunately, I was sorely disappointed after testing it. It has reasonably good suction, comparable to other hand-held vacuums, and it comes with two extra filters. Those are the only good things I can say about it. It does not have two speeds, as the instructions say. It seems as if the designers combined the worst aspects of a conventional vacuum with the worst aspects of a hand-held. The attachments are very flimsy and keep coming loose. The floor attachment does not work on carpets, and the brush and crevice attachments cannot be used with the extension pipes. The power head is heavy and poorly balanced, so tiring to hold. And it has a cord, which is an absolute nuisance, especially for cleaning the car.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This vacuum is easy to use, and it’s lightweight. It’s got a strong suction power, and I would recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Light weight. Has good suction. Sections come apart easily.
reviews.reviewText: This is what I think of as a starting out vacuum. It has good suction on hard surfaces. It isn’t great with cleaning carpet. It can pick up smaller pieces best, but it can clog up quickly. I had a difficult time keeping the pieces of the pipe together. I ended up putting some tape around it. It did much better after that. The dust bin opens and empties easy. I don’t feel like it is a great vacuum for carpet. But, it does pick up dirt and small pieces on hard surfaces. I have been using it as a designated cat litter clean up vacuum. It works pretty well for that purpose and my other vacuum doesn’t end up having a litter odor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Flimsy plastic with a ton of suction
reviews.reviewText: I have mixed feelings about this vacuum. It plugs into the wall, which afford it a lot of extra power in suction. However, it is very cheaply made, and the plastic is precariously thin. The wand is not very sturdy, and I am sure it will crack at some point soon. It doesn’t click into place, you have to force it on there. Attachments like that tend to eventually stop holding and just fall off, without a mechanism that clicks it in. The floor attachment doesn’t have a beater bar, so it’s not really good for any carpets. It works fine on hard floors again the suction power is the best thing about this vacuum. I don’t see this lasting very long, but I am enjoying using it while I have it. I just use it in my home office to do a quick tidy. I’m not using it across my whole home, but I do think it takes the place of a little mini vacuum for quick messes. I just wish it were better quality and the pieces didn’t seem so flimsy.
